     This study included analysis of a variety of modern, consumer-grade LiBs to determine the prevalence and mass loadings of bis-FMeSI, bis-FEtSI, and bis-FBSI. Eleven of 17 batteries contained bis-FASIs at mass loadings above the analytical detection limit (5 ng per battery). Mass loadings were variable ranging from 7.2 ng to 35.6 mg across a range of battery types and sizes (Supplementary Table

      7

